== 9...Nxe5 ==
The central pawns have been exchanged. White can, and should, play [[/10. Bf4|'''10. Bf4''']], developing the bishop and pinning the knight on e5. This also justifies White's previous move 8. g3.

White's knight on c4 is hanging, so there isn't many alternatives. 10. Nxe5? doesn't develop any of White's pieces and allows Black to quickly catch up in development.

